Description: About half of heavy foot and floor of Attic black-glazed pottery open vessel (stemless cup or cup-skyphos); glazed black save for resting surface and band at top of inside of foot; added red on fillet at join of foot and bowl; inscription incised on resting surface.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 515)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1889)
